AGI - Twelve hours to try to defuse the crisis and relaunch the dialogue: Emmanuel Macron, expected this evening in <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-05-20/new-caledonia-return-again-francia-per-independence-26457010/">New Caledonia</a>, plays his hand in the game with a last minute trip, facing two sides that seem unconcilable. "It's a poker game like that played at the Agricultural Exhibition" in February, with his visit in the middle of a revolt in the agricultural world, sums up a congressman of the presidential party Reinassance. "O doubles or nothing. It is a bet>", adds a ministerial councillor. Macron, taken off last night and waited Thursday around 8.30 in Noumea (the 23.30 of today's Italian time), put together his program during the flight, without even knowing who was willing to meet him, according to a high level source within the executive.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
The independent president of the New Caledonia government, Louis Mapou>, one of the main actors on the spot, was so informed of the journey from the media, according to a source close to the question. "It's all done in absolute improvisation", the source suspirates, believing that this surprise visit aims above all to create a shock effect in order to announce a postponement of the electoral reform that made fire to the powders. From the beginning of the riots, on May 13, six people were killed and many commercial activities and buildings were destroyed. Today the situation, even if quieter, remains precarious and whole neighborhoods are still difficult to access. The dialogue between separatists and "lists" is still. "In the macronist field we count on the visit of the Head of State to unlock the situation and we believe that the crisis can serve as an electric shock to advance the evolution of the institutional status of the island" said the source. The goal is to listen and make decisions, assuring the source of the executive.
< blockquote
&nbsp;
However, the risk remains great that separatists Kanak boycott the visit, as they did during the last presidential trip in July 2023
</blockquote
&nbsp;
Macron, who has overwhelmed his entire weekly programme in the middle of the European campaign, will have to remain there for twelve hours, or even more if necessary. Shortly after his arrival, he will meet the elected and economic actors to make the point of the situation in the archipelago, explained the Eliseo. The rest of the programme, especially the most political part, is still being defined. No details were given on the interlocutors who could meet him, after the refusal of his proposal for video conferencing last week. "Evidently, the visit has aroused astonishment and interest, but we cannot commit ourselves to the results that will be achieved," says Eliseo. For Jean-Philippe Derosier, professor of public law at the University of Lille, "it was necessary to take an initiative to calm the souls" and "now everything will depend on what the president will say. The separatists do not accept ultimatum, they are imbued with a culture other than ours in which space is given to time."
&nbsp;
<div </div
