&nbsp;
Israel had already given its ok to an agreement on the truce that provided for the release of Israeli hostages and Palestinian prisoners and a ceasefire of a few weeks. Just the change decided by the Egyptian intelligence, according to the US broadcaster, made the agreement naufragare on 6 May last. The conditions submitted to Hamas were different from those that had agreed on the other negotiators, Qatar and the United States, who together with Israel felt "untrained", blowing up the deal. Particularly embarrassed and angry about this incorrect operation would have been CIA director Bill Burns, according to CNN.&nbsp;

